        </figcaption>
        <div class="title article-text" id="dotonbori">
            <h2>
                Dotonbori: The Heart of Osaka's Nightlife
            </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="article-text">
            Dotonbori epitomizes Osaka's vibrant nightlife and culinary scene. This lively district dazzles with its neon signs and offers an endless variety of street food, from takoyaki to okonomiyaki. A walk along the Dotonbori River presents the perfect blend of scenic beauty and urban energy.
            <br><br>
            Don't miss the Glico Running Man sign for that iconic Osaka photo!
        </p>
        <img src="{{ asset('/assets/img/dotonbori.jpg') }}" class="article-image" alt="Dotonbori">
        <figcaption class="caption-text">
            Dotonbori © Japan Guide
        </figcaption>
        <div class="title article-text" id="dendenTown">
            <h2>
                DenDen Town: The Tech and Otaku Culture Hub
            </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="article-text">
            DenDen Town is a paradise for tech enthusiasts and anime fans. This district is filled with stores specializing in electronics, manga, and anime goods. Unique cafes and specialty shops provide a deep dive into Japan's otaku culture, making it a must-visit for anyone interested in the latest in tech and anime.
        </p>
        <div class="title article-text" id="shinsekai">
            <h2>
                Shinsekai and the Tsutenkaku Tower
            </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="article-text">
            Shinsekai, meaning "New World," offers a nostalgic look at post-war Japan. The Tsutenkaku Tower, standing tall at 108m, offers panoramic views of Osaka. The area's retro charm and delicious kushikatsu (fried skewer) bars invite visitors to explore and indulge.
            <br><br>
            Got a head for heights? Try walking out on to 'TIP THE TSUTENKAKU', a glass-bottomed viewing platform jutting out from the tower! It's not for the faint of heart at 92.5m above ground...
            <br><br>
            If that's a little too nail biting for you, why not have a go on the TOWER SLIDER, a 60-metre long slide that curves its way around the east elevator tower? Don't worry - there's no glass bottom on this slide!
        </p>
        <div class="block-quote">
            <p>
                <a href="https://affiliate.klook.com/redirect?aid=38574&aff_adid=825574&k_site=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.klook.com%2Factivity%2F76766-osaka-tsutenkaku-admission-ticket%2F%3Fspm%3DSearchResult.SearchSuggest_LIST%26clickId%3Dcb6ee3b4ab" target="_blank">Book your entry ticket to Tsutenkaku Tower here</a> (¥900). Once there, you can book your ticket for Tip The Tsutenkaku (¥300) and the Tower Slider (¥1,000)
            </p>
        </div>
        <img src="{{ asset('/assets/img/shinsekai.jpg') }}" class="article-image" alt="Shinsekai">
        <figcaption class="caption-text">
            Tsutenkaku Tower © Japan Guide
        </figcaption>
        <div class="title article-text" id="streetFood">
            <h2>
                The Culinary Adventure: Sampling Osaka's Street Food
            </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="article-text">
            Osaka is often dubbed the nation's kitchen, and a culinary adventure here is a must. The city's street food, including takoyaki, okonomiyaki, and kushikatsu, represents the essence of Osaka's food culture. Exploring the food stalls and markets is an experience in itself.
            <br><br>
            If you truly want to experience the food culture of Osaka, take a guided food tour of Kuromon Market! This is the best way to experience the city's food with a local to guide the way.
        </p>
        <img src="{{ asset('/assets/img/kuromon.jpg') }}" class="article-image" alt="Kuromon Market">
        <figcaption class="caption-text">
            Kuromon Market © Japan Guide
        </figcaption>
