        </figcaption>
        <div class="title article-text" id="shinsaibashi">
            <h2>
                Shopping in Shinsaibashi: A Shopper's Paradise
            </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="article-text">
            Shinsaibashi, Osaka's premier shopping district, blends traditional and modern retail experiences. Whether you're after high fashion, souvenirs, or the latest gadgets, Shinsaibashi's covered shopping arcade caters to every need and budget, ensuring a shopper's delight.
        </p>
        <img src="{{ asset('/assets/img/shinsaibashi.jpg') }}" class="article-image" alt="Shinsaibashi">
        <figcaption class="caption-text">
            Shinsaibashi © Japan Guide
        </figcaption>
        <div class="title article-text" id="itinerary">
            <h2>
                Osaka Itinerary: Planning Your Visit
            </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="article-text">
            Creating the perfect Osaka itinerary involves balancing visits to historical sites with modern attractions. This guide serves as a starting point for discovering Osaka's diverse offerings, from its historical wonders to its modern marvels.
        </p>
        <p class="article-text">
            Osaka's blend of historical and modern attractions makes it a unique destination within Japan. This guide to the top ten things to do in Osaka invites travelers to explore a city where every corner offers new discoveries and where each visit promises unforgettable memories.
        </p>
        <img src="{{ asset('/assets/img/osakaculture.jpg') }}" class="article-image" alt="Musician in Osaka Castle Park">
        <figcaption class="caption-text">
            Traditional Musician in Osaka Castle Park © Japan Guide
        </figcaption>
        <div class="title article-text" id="faqs">
            <h2>
                FAQs
            </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="article-text">
            * <span style="color: plum">Best time to visit Osaka?</span><br>Spring and autumn offer pleasant weather and beautiful scenery, making them ideal times to visit.
            <br><br>
            * <span style="color: plum">How to get around in Osaka?</span><br>Osaka's extensive public transportation system, including subways, trains, and buses, makes it easy to navigate the city. Pick up the <strong><a href="https://affiliate.klook.com/redirect?aid=38574&aff_adid=825574&k_site=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.klook.com%2Factivity%2F11515-osaka-metro-1-2-day-pass-osaka%2F">Osaka Metro Pass</a></strong> to easily get around.
            <br><br>
            * <span style="color: plum">What are some off-the-beaten-path activities in Osaka?</span><br>Visiting the Instant Ramen Museum, exploring Amerika-mura, and relaxing in an onsen offer unique experiences beyond the typical tourist path.
            <br><br>
            * <span style="color: plum">Tips for budget travelers in Osaka?</span><br>Utilize the <strong><a href="https://affiliate.klook.com/redirect?aid=38574&aff_adid=825574&k_site=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.klook.com%2Factivity%2F82312-amazing-pass-osaka%2F">Osaka Amazing Pass</a></strong>, dine at local markets, and consider staying in guesthouses or capsule hotels for a budget-friendly trip.
            <br><br>
            * <span style="color: plum">How many days are recommended for an Osaka itinerary?</span><br>Three to four days allow for a comprehensive exploration of Osaka's major attractions, though there's always more to discover with additional time.
            <br><br>
            * <span style="color: plum">Safety tips for travelers in Osaka?</span><br>Osaka is generally safe, but as with any major city, it's wise to stay vigilant, especially in crowded areas, and secure your valuables.
        </p>
